<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Should I build a native iOS app or use cross-platform? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>Native Swift gives the best performance, deepest Apple ecosystem integration, and access to advanced features like ARKit, HealthKit, and Core ML. Ideal for apps using augmented reality, health data, or requiring cutting-edge performance. Cross-platform suits apps needing iOS+Android parity with code sharing. We recommend native Swift when performance and Apple ecosystem depth are critical.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How long does it take to build and launch an iOS app? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>MVP: 8-14 weeks. Feature-rich consumer or enterprise app: 4-9 months. Apple review via App Store Connect typically takes 1-3 days. We use agile sprints with working builds every 2 weeks, so you can validate and adjust continuously throughout development.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Do you handle App Store submission and compliance? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes, full App Store submission including metadata, screenshots, App Preview video, privacy labels, and App Store Review Guideline compliance. We've achieved 100% first-submission approval rate on our last 35+ submissions because we build to Apple's standards from day one.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Can you build for iPhone, iPad, and Apple Watch? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. Universal apps supporting iPhone and iPad with adaptive layouts, watchOS apps for Apple Watch, and App Clips for lightweight experiences. We support iOS 15+ to maximize feature access including SwiftUI, Async/Await, and the latest Apple frameworks.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How do you integrate with Apple's health and payment frameworks? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>We integrate HealthKit for health data access, StoreKit 2 for subscriptions and in-app purchases, Apple Pay for seamless payments, PassKit for digital wallets, and Sign in with Apple for privacy-first authentication. Deep Apple ecosystem integration is our expertise.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Can you integrate Face ID and biometric authentication? <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. We implement Face ID and Touch ID using LocalAuthentication framework, Secure Enclave integration, and Keychain secure storage for biometric credentials. This provides enterprise-grade security while maintaining a seamless user experience compliant with Apple's security guidelines.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

